        "title": "Spring Security BCrypt always look for \u201c$2a\u201d regex",
        "body": "<p>I am implementing <code>Spring Security<\/code> with <code>Spring Boot<\/code>. And I've generated password online using <code>BCrypt<\/code> generator. But when I try to login I got the error message:<\/p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>2019-10-18 11:10:56.983  WARN 53908 --- [io-9090-exec-10]\no.s.s.c.bcrypt.BCryptPasswordEncoder     : Encoded password does not\nlook like BCrypt.<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n<p>After some research, I found out that there is a bug in <code>Spring Security<\/code> where <code>BCrypt<\/code> only looks for <code>$2a<\/code> regex. Can anyone explain to me to solve these issues?<\/p>\n",
